Description: Foot sherd of Attic black glaze pottery skyphos; glazed black on interior and exterior; moulded ring foot, profile not fully preserved - inner surface lost, exterior has concave upper member with reddish miltos wash; convex lower member in two degrees, the upper part glazed black (worn); reddish miltos wash in groove between the two degrees); underside reserved with reddish miltos wash, black band at perimeter and trace of another nearer centre; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1273)
